videos.headline: Vaibhav Arora to Shivam Dube, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Full and straight at 137kph, in the slot for Dube to slog but he's beaten completely. Off stump goes out of the ground. Shivam Dube b Vaibhav Arora 28(18) [4s-1 6s-3]

Narine to Mitchell, out Bowled!! Right through the gate! Mitchell dances down for a lofted shot, isn't quite to the pitch of this off-break and it turns between bat and pad before crashing into middle. Narine punches the air and Mitchell nods his head to acknowledge that he was completely done in there. Mitchell b Narine 25(19) [4s-1 6s-1]

Vaibhav Arora to Ravindra, out Caught by Chakaravarthy!! Straight to long-on. Ravindra takes it on a length outside off, lofts and straightaway he knew he had made a mistake. Did he not know there was a fielder there? Ravindra falls to a cheap score again. Ravindra c Chakaravarthy b Vaibhav Arora 15(8) [4s-3]

Mustafizur to Starc, out Caught by Ravindra!! Good idea but Starc finds the fielder. Gets across outside off, gets under the short ball and it's down deep backward square leg's throat. Ravindra moves across to take a smart catch. Starc c Ravindra b Mustafizur 0(3)

Mustafizur to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by Jadeja!! Another miscue and Jadeja takes it so easily at deep mid-wicket. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, Shreyas Iyer slogs and does not find the middle of the bat, finds Jadeja. Shreyas Iyer c Jadeja b Mustafizur 34(32) [4s-3]

Tushar Deshpande to Russell, out Caught by Mitchell!! Bravo claps Tushar Deshpande after he gets Russell. Was in the slot, fullish outside off, Russell lofts but picks out long-on and Mitchell takes another catch, just inside the cushions. A few more yards and would have been six. Massive wicket as that wicket could make a difference of 10-15 to the final total. Russell c Mitchell b Tushar Deshpande 10(10) [4s-2]

Tushar Deshpande to Rinku Singh, out Bowled!! Dragged back on. Full outside off, Rinku Singh goes for a big drive, thick inside-edge is back on the stumps, was the slower ball and away from the left-hander. Rinku Singh b Tushar Deshpande 9(14)

Theekshana to Ramandeep Singh, out Bowled!! Theekshana has the last laugh! Ramandeep Singh makes room to play this, but Theekshana bowls a carrom ball and directs it at the stumps. Ramandeep gets beaten as the ball zips through and finds the middle stump rattled. CSK spinners owning KKR batters in front of the Chepauk crowd. Ramandeep Singh b Theekshana 13(12) [6s-1]

Jadeja to Venkatesh Iyer, out Caught by Mitchell!! Venkatesh Iyer's struggle comes to an end. Walks back after playing a rusty knock as Jadeja is on absolute fire. Goes short and quick around middle, Venkatesh Iyer pulls it towards mid-wicket where Mitchell completes a fine running catch to his right. That shall also be the strategic timeout.. Venkatesh Iyer c Mitchell b Jadeja 3(8)

Jadeja to Narine, out Caught by Theekshana!! Jadeja strikes twice in his first over. Gets the wicket of the danger man - Sunil Narine. Width on offer outside off and Narine looks to take him on. Throws his hands at this widish delivery and miscues it towards wide long-off. Theekshana stationed in the deep takes a safe reverse cup and that's that from Narine with the bat. Didn't look comfortable since that shoulder niggle, but hopefully it's nothing serious. Narine c Theekshana b Jadeja 27(20) [4s-3 6s-2]

Jadeja to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, out Lbw!! Jadeja strikes on his first ball, just like Tushar Deshpande did earlier in the innings. A flatter delivery on middle and leg, Angkrish Raghuvanshi tries to be cheeky, goes for the reverse sweep and gets rapped on the pads. The bowler goes up in an appeal and up goes the umpire's finger as well. The young batsman walks back after playing a handy cameo. Doesn't bother of taking a review, because this looked out.. Angkrish Raghuvanshi lbw b Jadeja 24(18) [4s-3 6s-1]

Tushar Deshpande to Philip Salt, out Caught by Jadeja!! Tushar Deshpande strikes on the first ball! Back of a length outside off, Philip Salt throws his hands at it, carves it towards backward point where Jadeja takes a sharp catch. Philip Salt departs without troubling the scorers. Philip Salt c Jadeja b Tushar Deshpande 0(1)
